<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The call strncpy(str + WS_KEY_LEN, WS_GUID, WS_GUID_LEN + 1) writes the GUID plus its terminating NUL into str, but the SHA1Input call that follows uses an explicit length WS_KEY_GUID_LEN (WS_KEY_LEN + WS_GUID_LEN) and the buffer is not used as a NUL-terminated string before being freed. The written terminating NUL is never read, so removing the +1 (and thus not writing the NUL) would not change program behaviour. Therefore this operation is dead code and violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2.
</scenario>
